&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Registered General Practitioner – Sessional&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The North East Ambulance Service are seeking sessional GP&#39;s to work in our Clinical Assessment Service (CAS) supporting the NHS 111 and 999 services.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is to support forward strategies around winter planning and the NHS 111 First “Talk Before You Walk” model.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the CAS you will work within a multi-disciplinary team comprising Advanced Practitioners, Pharmacists and Administrative support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The CAS provides both in hours and out of hours remote assessment for those cases triaged via a clinician triage. As a Sessional GP you may also be asked to support the ambulance dispatch function, supporting our clinicians or undertaking calls to those cases triaged to ambulance dispositions. As such you will be contributing to the achievement of those targets around Hear and Treat and NHS 111 key performance indicators.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Feedback and support - both ongoing and in relation to revalidation - will be provided through a managerial structure that includes a Lead GP and Deputy Medical Director.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates must be able to undertake remote assessment utilising both telephone and video. Home visits are also an integral part of the role supporting with our out of hours palliative service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sites are located at&lt;strong&gt; Newburn&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Hebburn&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shifts will comprise a combination of both on site and home-based working as an option.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Competitive sessional rates offered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
